  "text": "The SCID FOX Chase female mice (8-9 weeks old) were intravenously (i.v.) inoculated with 2 £ 10 [CITATION_1] Raji cells (mix of 3 clones with either empty or sgFOXO1 vector). Mice were intraperitoneally (i.p.) treated with rituximab (10 mg/kg) three times a week starting on day 5 after inoculation of tumor cells. Bioluminescence was measured once a week (starting from the day of injection). Mice were i.p. injected with D-luciferin (150 mg/ kg), anaesthetized with isoflurane and visualized using IVIS Imaging System (Xenogen, Alameda, CA, USA). Images were analyzed with the Living Image 4.2 software (Caliper Life Science, Hopkinton, MA, USA). Statistical significance was determined with the Mann-Whitney Rank Sum test.",
